title: UK Top 40 Chart Show November 19 1983
description:
This the UK Top 40 retro chart countdown, with DJColzz, playing some of those from the lower regions of the chart, as well as the entire top 20 singles. He also digs into the album chart of the week. Chart facts and chat in-between, but it is all about the music.
Going back to 1983, music from The Cure; Donna Summer; Thompson Twins; Aztec Camera; Eurythmics; Adam Ant and many more.
The top end of the chart has a battle for supremacy between McCartney/Jackson, Shakinâ€™ Stevens and Billy Joel. Who will reign the King of Pop in November 1983. This is the official chart, supplied by the Official Charts Company.

Two hours of fun and music.
